 2, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": null, "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": null, "UrduDescription": null, "English": "Allah’s (s.w.t) choicest blessings be upon Mohammed and his holy progeny.", "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": "Parwardigaar Tu rehmat naazil farma Hazrat Muhammad (s.a.w.a) aur unki Aal (a.s) par.", "Urdu": "اے معبود! رحمت نازل فرما حضرت محمدؐ اور انکی آل ؑپر۔", "RArabic": "ALLAHUMMA SWALLE ALAA MUHAMMADIW WA AALE MUHAMMADIN", "ArabicText1": "اَللّٰهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَّآلِ مُحَمَّدٍ۔", "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, "ArabicText9": null, "ArabicGreenSign9": null, "ArabicRedSign9": null, "ArabicBlueSign9": null, "ArabicText10": null, "ArabicGreenSign10": null, "ArabicRedSign10": null, "ArabicBlueSign10": null, "ArabicText11": null, "ArabicGreenSign11": null, "ArabicRedSign11": null, "ArabicBlueSign11": null, "ArabicText12": null, "ArabicGreenSign12": null, "ArabicRedSign12": null, "ArabicBlueSign12": null, "ArabicText13": null, "ArabicGreenSign13": null, "ArabicRedSign13": null, "ArabicBlueSign13": null, "ArabicText14": null, "ArabicGreenSign14": null, "ArabicRedSign14": null, "ArabicBlueSign14": null, "ArabicText15": null, "ArabicGreenSign15": null, "ArabicRedSign15": null, "ArabicBlueSign15": null, "ArabicText16": null, "ArabicGreenSign16": null, "ArabicRedSign16": null, "ArabicBlueSign16": null, "ArabicText17": null, "ArabicGreenSign17": null, "ArabicRedSign17": null, "ArabicBlueSign17": null, "ArabicText18": null, "ArabicGreenSign18": null, "ArabicRedSign18": null, "ArabicBlueSign18": null, "ArabicText19": null, "ArabicGreenSign19": null, "ArabicRedSign19": null, "ArabicBlueSign19": null, "ArabicText20": null, "ArabicGreenSign20": null, "ArabicRedSign20": null, "ArabicBlueSign20": null, "EnglishImage": null, "GujaratiImage": null, "RUrduImage": null, "UrduImage": null, "IsRed": 0, "MinimizeDescriptionLine": 0, "IsPrintable": 0}, {"Id": 1017312, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "Then you will be provided with your sustenance and livelihood before the sunrise on Saturday. Ahmad bin Mabindaz, the narrator of this Hadith, says: I asked Abu Ja far Mohammad bin Othman bin Saeed Amri that if someone wishes to offer this prayer and supplication for sustenance but doesn’t live in the city of Medina, what should he do? He said: Perform the Ziyarat of my Master and Leader, Prophet Mohammad (s), in the shrine of the Imam of his city or land, near the grave of that Imam. I asked: If there isn’t any grave of the holy Imams in his city, what shall he do? He said: He should visit a few noblemen and believers, then go towards the desert and perform that which has been commanded in the Ziyarat in the right portion of the desert. If Allah wills, this action will result in his prosperity and success.", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Agar is amaal ko anjaam do to abhi roz-e-Shambah (Sunday) na aayega keh tumhari navi rozi aa jayegi. Ahmed bin Mabandaaz (is hadees ke raawi) kehte hai: Muhammad bin Usman bin Saeed Amri se kaha: jo rozi ke liye dua karna chahte hu agar shaher-e-Madina mein ho to kya kare? Farmaya: jis Imam (a) ka Haram us shaher mein ho us mein jaaye aur Hazrat (a) ke sirhaane (sar ki taraf) hamare sayed o sardaar Rasool-e-Khuda (s) ki ziyarat kare. Ham ne jo kaha kiya agar khud uske shaher mein kisi bhi Imam ki qabr na ho to kya kare? Farmaya: Salaha aur barguzida afraad mein se ek ki ziyarat kare aur sehra mein jaaye aur sehra ke daahine (right) taraf ham ne jo kaha usey anjaam de, insha-Allah us ki haajat poori hogi.", "UrduDescription": "اگر اس عمل کو انجام دو تو ابھی روز شنبہ (اتوار) نہ آئیگا کہ تمہاری نئی روزی آجائے گی۔ احمد بن مابنداذ (اس حدیث کے راوی) کہتے ہیں: محمد بن عثمان بن سعید عمری سے کہا: جو روزی کے لئے دعا کرنا چاہتا ہو اگر شہر مدینہ میں نہ ہو تو کیا کرے؟ فرمایا: جس امامؑ کا حرم اس شہر میں ہو اس میں جائے اور حضرتؑ کے سرہانے ہمارے سید و سردار رسول خداؐ کی زیارت کرے۔ ہم نے عرض کیا: اگر خود اس کے شہر میں کسی امام کا مرقد نہ ہو تو کیا کرے؟ فرمایا: صلحاء اور برگزیدہ افراد میں سے کسی ایک کی زیارت کرے اور صحرا میں جائے اور صحرا کے داہنی طرف ہم نے جو کہا اس کو انجام دے انشاء اللہ اس کی حاجت پوری ہوگی۔", "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, "ArabicText9": null, "ArabicGreenSign9": null, "ArabicRedSign9": null, "Arabic